            {
              "file": "bench-artifacts/cache-api.md",
              "patch": "Index: bench-artifacts/cache-api.md\n===================================================================\n--- bench-artifacts/cache-api.md\t\n+++ bench-artifacts/cache-api.md\t\n@@ -0,0 +1,53 @@\n+# Cache API\n+\n+Exported from `cache.mjs` in the [`cache.mjs`](cache.mjs).\n+\n+## createCache()\n+\n+Creates a cache instance with `get`, `set`, `delete`, and `clear` methods.\n+\n+### Usage\n+\n+```js\n+import { createCache } from './cache.mjs'\n+\n+const cache = createCache()\n+```\n+\n+### Methods\n+\n+The returned object has the following methods:\n+\n+#### get(key)\n+\n+Retrieves a value from the cache by key.\n+\n+```js\n+cache.get(key) // returns value or undefined\n+```\n+\n+#### set(key, value)\n+\n+Sets a value in the cache by key and returns the value.\n+\n+```js\n+cache.set(key, value) // returns value\n+```\n+\n+#### delete(key)\n+\n+Deletes a value from the cache by key and returns `true` if the key existed, `false` otherwise.\n+\n+```js\n+cache.delete(key) // returns true or false\n+```\n+\n+#### clear()\n+\n+Clears all entries from the cache.\n+\n+```js\n+cache.clear()\n+```\n+\n+The cache uses an in-memory `Map` to store values.\n",
              "additions": 53,
              "deletions": 0,
              "status": "added"
            }
          ]
        },
